{#
  /tools/sec-edgar-venezuela-impairment-search

  Pre-canned SEC EDGAR full-text search for Venezuela / PDVSA / impairment
  / contingent-liability disclosures across S&P 500 filers.

  This is the tool wrapping for the same engine that powers the
  per-company "Venezuela exposure" landing pages. It targets the
  high-intent GSC query "sec edgar venezuela or sanctions or contingent
  liabilities or impairment or pdvsa" which currently lands users on
  generic /companies pages with poor relevance.

  Sections (this order mirrors the JSON-LD breadcrumb):
    1. Hero + custom-search box (free-text → company landing page).
    2. Pre-canned preset cards (one click → EDGAR full-text search).
    3. Curated company quick-jump table (known disclosers).
    4. Methodology / FAQ block.
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}
{% from "_cluster_nav.html.j2" import cluster_nav %}

{% block head_extra %}
<style>
  .edgar-hero { background: var(--sr-gray-bg); border-left: 4px solid var(--sr-blue); padding: 18px 22px; margin: 16px 0 28px; }
  .edgar-hero h2 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--sr-blue-dark); font-size: 18px; }
  .edgar-hero p { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--sr-dark-text); }

  .edgar-search { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin: 16px 0 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .edgar-search input[type="text"] { flex: 1; min-width: 240px; padding: 10px 14px; border: 1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); border-radius: 3px; font-size: 14px; }
  .edgar-search button { padding: 10px 22px; background: var(--sr-red); color: var(--white); border: none; border-radius: 3px; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; font-size: 14px; }

  .preset-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin: 8px 0 28px; }
  .preset-card { border: 1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); border-left: 4px solid var(--sr-blue); border-radius: 3px; padding: 16px 18px; background: var(--white); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
  .preset-card h3 { font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--sr-blue-dark); font-size: 16px; margin: 0; }
  .preset-card .question { font-size: 13px; color: var(--sr-gray-text); font-style: italic; margin: 0; }
  .preset-card .why { font-size: 13px; color: var(--sr-dark-text); margin: 0; }
  .preset-card .meta { font-size: 11px; color: var(--sr-gray-text); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.6px; margin-top: auto; }
  .preset-card .meta strong { color: var(--sr-blue-dark); }
  .preset-card .cta { display: inline-block; padding: 8px 14px; background: var(--sr-blue); color: var(--white); border-radius: 3px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 13px; text-decoration: none; align-self: flex-start; }
  .preset-card .cta:hover { background: var(--sr-red); }

  table.disclosers { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; margin: 8px 0 24px; }
  table.disclosers th, table.disclosers td { padding: 10px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
  table.disclosers th { background: var(--sr-gray-bg); font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--sr-blue-dark); font-size: 13px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.6px; }
  table.disclosers td.ticker { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 700; color: var(--sr-blue-dark); white-space: nowrap; }
  table.disclosers td.level .pill { display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.6px; border-radius: 999px; color: var(--white); }
  table.disclosers td.level .pill.direct     { background: var(--sr-red); }
  table.disclosers td.level .pill.indirect   { background: #f5b041; }
  table.disclosers td.level .pill.historical { background: var(--sr-blue); }
  table.disclosers td.actions a { display: inline-block; margin-right: 8px; font-size: 13px; }

  .disclaimer { background: #fff3e0; border-left: 4px solid #f5b041; padding: 14px 18px; font-size: 13px; color: #7c4a03; margin: 24px 0; border-radius: 3px; }

  .faq-block details { border: 1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); border-left: 3px solid var(--sr-blue); border-radius: 3px; padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; background: var(--white); }
  .faq-block details[open] { border-left-color: var(--sr-red); }
  .faq-block summary { font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--sr-blue-dark); font-weight: 700; font-size: 16px; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; }
  .faq-block summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-block summary::before { content: "▸ "; color: var(--sr-red); font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-block details[open] summary::before { content: "▾ "; }
  .faq-block .faq-answer { font-size: 14px; color: var(--sr-dark-text); margin-top: 10px; line-height: 1.55; }
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<section class="container">

  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a><span>/</span>
    <a href="/tools">Tools</a><span>/</span>
    <span>SEC EDGAR Venezuela / PDVSA / Impairment Search</span>
  </nav>

  <header style="margin: 16px 0 20px;">
    <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:#cc0000; font-weight:700;">
      Compliance &amp; research tool · Updated {{ today_human }}
    </div>
    <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:32px; color:var(--sr-blue-dark); margin:8px 0 10px;">
      SEC EDGAR Venezuela &amp; PDVSA Disclosure Search
    </h1>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-style:italic; color:var(--sr-gray-text); font-size:17px;">
      Pre-canned full-text searches across the SEC EDGAR corpus for any
      mention of Venezuela, PDVSA, CITGO, impairment charges, contingent
      liabilities, or sanctions exposure in 10-K, 20-F, 10-Q, and 8-K
      filings.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="edgar-hero">
    <h2>What this does</h2>
    <p>
      SEC EDGAR's full-text search is free and powerful but the UI is
      hostile to the questions analysts actually ask. This tool packages
      seven of the most common Venezuela-research queries — written by
      someone who has spent too many hours in <code>efts.sec.gov</code> —
      so you can launch them with one click, with the right form filter
      and date window already applied.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each preset opens directly on EDGAR. If you want a sourced,
      pre-analysed answer for a specific S&amp;P 500 ticker instead, type
      the company below — we'll route you to its Venezuela-exposure
      profile page (OFAC SDN match, EDGAR scan, news corpus, all in one
      place).
    </p>
  </div>

  {# ── Custom company lookup ─────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <h2 id="company-lookup">Look up a specific S&amp;P 500 company</h2>
  <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--sr-dark-text);">
    Type a name (e.g. <em>Chevron</em>, <em>Halliburton</em>) or ticker
    (<em>CVX</em>, <em>HAL</em>, <em>SLB</em>). We resolve to the
    canonical Venezuela-exposure profile for that ticker, which already
    includes the EDGAR full-text scan results inline.
  </p>
  <form method="get"
        action="/tools/public-company-venezuela-exposure-check"
        class="edgar-search">
    <input type="text" name="q"
           placeholder="Chevron, Halliburton, CVX, SLB, HAL…"
           autocomplete="off" required />
    <button type="submit">Open exposure profile →</button>
  </form>

  {# ── Pre-canned EDGAR search presets ───────────────────────────── #}
  <h2 id="presets">Pre-canned EDGAR research queries</h2>
  <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--sr-dark-text);">
    Each card below opens an SEC EDGAR full-text search with the query,
    form types, and date window already filled in. You can edit any of
    them on EDGAR's UI once it loads.
  </p>

  <div class="preset-grid">
    {% for p in presets %}
    <div class="preset-card">
      <h3>{{ p.title }}</h3>
      <p class="question">"{{ p.question }}"</p>
      <p class="why">{{ p.why }}</p>
      <div class="meta">
        <strong>Forms:</strong> {{ p.forms|join(', ') }} ·
        <strong>Window:</strong> last {{ (p.lookback_days / 365)|round(1) }} years
      </div>
      <a class="cta" href="{{ p.url() }}" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">
        Run on EDGAR →
      </a>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  {# ── Curated quick-jump: known disclosers ──────────────────────── #}
  {% if disclosers %}
  <h2 id="known-disclosers">Curated S&amp;P 500 companies known to disclose Venezuela</h2>
  <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--sr-dark-text);">
    These {{ disclosers|length }} S&amp;P 500 tickers have a documented,
    hand-curated Venezuela exposure on the Caracas Research register —
    direct operations, indirect subsidiary exposure, or historical
    impairments. Each row links to the full Venezuela-exposure profile
    and to a pre-canned EDGAR search filtered to that company's CIK.
  </p>

  <table class="disclosers">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Ticker</th>
        <th>Company</th>
        <th>Exposure</th>
        <th>One-line note</th>
        <th>Open</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for d in disclosers %}
      <tr>
        <td class="ticker">{{ d.ticker }}</td>
        <td>{{ d.short_name }}</td>
        <td class="level">
          <span class="pill {{ d.exposure_level }}">{{ d.exposure_level }}</span>
        </td>
        <td>{{ d.one_line }}</td>
        <td class="actions">
          <a href="{{ d.profile_url }}">Profile</a>
          <a href="{{ d.edgar_search_url }}" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">EDGAR</a>
        </td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p style="font-size:14px;">
    <a href="/companies"><strong>Browse the full S&amp;P 500 Venezuela exposure register →</strong></a>
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  {# ── Methodology / disclaimer ──────────────────────────────────── #}
  <div class="disclaimer">
    <strong>Methodology &amp; disclaimer.</strong>
    All preset queries deeplink into the SEC's official
    <code>efts.sec.gov</code> full-text search; we don't proxy or
    intercept the request. The curated company list is maintained by
    Caracas Research analysts and reviewed quarterly. Results from
    EDGAR are not legal or compliance advice — verify the underlying
    filing and consult qualified sanctions counsel before relying on a
    disclosure for a transaction.
  </div>

  {# ── FAQ (also rendered as FAQPage JSON-LD in the head) ────────── #}
  {% if faq %}
  <h2 id="faq">Frequently asked questions</h2>
  <section class="faq-block">
    {% for f in faq %}
    <details {% if loop.first %}open{% endif %}>
      <summary>{{ f.q }}</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">{{ f.a }}</div>
    </details>
    {% endfor %}
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  {{ cluster_nav(cluster_ctx) }}

  {% from "_recent_briefings.html.j2" import recent_briefings_rail %}
  {{ recent_briefings_rail(
       recent_briefings,
       heading="Latest analysis",
       intro="Recent investor briefings on SEC disclosures, impairments, and US-listed Venezuela exposure.",
  ) }}
</section>
{% endblock %}
